me.taylorkelly.mywarp.storage

Class AsyncWritingWarpStorage

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.google.common.collect.ForwardingObject
      • me.taylorkelly.mywarp.storage.AsyncWritingWarpStorage
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    WarpSource, WarpStorage

    public class AsyncWritingWarpStorage
extends com.google.common.collect.ForwardingObject
    A WarpStorage that works on top of another WarpStorage and executes every writing task asynchronous on a specified Executor.

    • Constructor Detail

      • AsyncWritingWarpStorage

        public AsyncWritingWarpStorage(WarpStorage warpStorage,
                               java.util.concurrent.Executor executor)
        Creates an instance. Every call is delegated to the given WarpStorage, writing methods are executed in the given Executor, reading methods still run in the thread that calls the method.
        Parameters:
        warpStorage - the WarpStorage whose writing methods should be executed asynchronous
        executor - the Executor that executes writing methods
